\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Dog Parks Directory\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"i\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bi bi-chevron-right\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"strong\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Austin\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-eyebrow\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Heat-proof indoor runs\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h1\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"Indoor dog park in Austin\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-chip-row\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-chip\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"chip-label\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Heat alert system\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"chip-value\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Active at 95°F+\\\"}],\\\"$undefined\\\"]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-chip\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"chip-label\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Coworking zones\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"chip-value\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Wi-Fi included\\\"}],\\\"$undefined\\\"]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"hero-description\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Tech hub culture meets extreme summer heat—Austin indoor dog parks combine AC, coworking spaces, and heat alerts so your pup stays active even when temps hit 100°F+.\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"city-rich-description\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-description-paragraph\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Austin’s vibrant dog culture uniquely matches the city’s tech-forward, social, and outdoorsy lifestyle while addressing the challenge of brutal Texas summers. With temperatures regularly exceeding 100°F from June through September, indoor facilities have become essential sanctuaries. Neighborhoods like the Domain and East Austin host innovative concepts that blend high-end AC with coworking hubs, coffee bars, and local breweries. These \\\\\\\"brew-and-play\\\\\\\" venues align with Austin’s remote-work culture, providing high-speed Wi-Fi and quiet zones alongside premium K9 turf and monitored play pods. Data from \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L12\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://www.austintexas.gov/department/parks-and-recreation\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-link\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Austin Parks and Recreation\\\"}],null,\\\" highlights numerous outdoor options, but the private indoor sector thrives by offering a specialized, temperature-controlled experience that is practically a requirement for safe year-round play.\\\"]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-description-paragraph\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"The operational focus of Austin’s indoor parks is rooted in transparency and community health. Top-tier facilities require a multi-step onboarding process, including a temperament evaluation and digital verification of Rabies, Distemper, and Bordetella vaccinations. Membership models are popular, with average monthly rates ranging from $120 to $180, often including perks like craft beverage credits, priority entry during heat alerts, and guest passes for housemates. For the casual visitor, $18 to $25 weekday drop-ins are common. Safety is enhanced through professional \\\\\\\"pack leaders\\\\\\\" and advanced hydration stations that provide filtered, chilled water. Owners can find more specific advice on managing their dogs during peak heat in our \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L12\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"#planning-essentials\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"rich-link\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"planning essentials\\\"}],null,\\\" guide. By integrating Austin hospitality with pet safety, these indoor parks have become indispensable anchors for the city’s pet parents.\\\"]}]]}],\\\"$L31\\\",\\\